•	The Fractal Reality: A mode sitting at $\lambda = 0.61$ is "barely" visible (near the $\phi^{-1}$ edge). A mode at $\lambda = 0.3$ is "strongly" visible. In standard chemistry, both count as "1." In RCFT, the first might be a "0.1 Valence" (weak bond) and the second a "0.9 Valence" (strong bond).
