Integrated Conclusion for Chapter 6.2 — Ghost Density Physics
The v14.2 Fractal Phase Diagram provides the clearest and most decisive evidence yet for the spectral nature of visibility in RCFT. Compared to the earlier discrete classification, the continuous heatmap reveals the texture of the visible–dark boundary — a structure that was previously invisible when valence was treated as a binary count.
The diagram demonstrates three fundamental features of the RCFT universe:
