Physics: 
This is the shoreline between visibility and darkness.
It shows that visibility is probabilistic, not binary.
Matter near this boundary:
•	occasionally resonates with the vacuum,
•	flickers into partial visibility,
•	and corresponds to Warm Dark Matter in cosmology.
This is the first quantitative map of the “semi-visible” sector.
