Between the cyan and white contours lies a broad, smooth gradient of fractal valence:
[ 0.1 < V < 0.9. ]
Physics: 
This is the Biological Zone — the region where matter is neither fully dark nor fully crystalline. It is flexible, dynamic, and spectrally responsive.
This region validates Theorem 6.2.B (Band Edge Fractionalization):
•	modes near φ recursive boundaries contribute fractional valence,
