•	conformational changes,
•	and catalytic transitions.
Life requires this fractal regime.
If the transition from visible to dark were a sharp cliff, biology could not exist.
________________________________________
4. The Stability Floor (The Red Dashed Line — φ⁻¹²)
Observation: 
The red line marks the φ⁻¹² stability floor — the theoretical lower bound for vibrational modes.
Physics: 
Above this line, almost no spectral activity survives.
This is the event horizon of the dark sector:
•	Sp(8) inertia overwhelms SO(9) geometry,
•	eigenvalues collapse below the stability floor,
•	and the system becomes spectrally silent.
This is the mathematical definition of deep dark matter.
